iffs-reactions-commentators-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esweeping%20tariff%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublican%20Sen.%20Charles%20Grassley%20of%20Iowa%20and%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Maria%20Cantwell%20of%20Washington%20on%20Thursday%20introduced%20a%20Senate%20bill%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-newsom-trump-tariffs-response-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elimit%20a%20president's%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20impose%20tariffs.%20The%20bill%20would%20allow%20Congress%20to%20vote%20to%20end%20any%20tariff%20at%20any%20time%2C%20require%20the%20president%20to%20provide%20Congress%20with%2048%20hours'%20notice%20before%20imposing%20any%20new%20duties%2C%20and%20require%20Congress%20to%20explicitly%20approve%20any%20new%20tariffs%20within%2060%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20additional%20Republicans%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0Mitch%20McConnell%20of%20Kentucky%2C%20Lisa%20Murkowski%20of%20Alaska%2C%20Thom%20Tillis%20of%20North%20Carolina%2C%20and%20Jerry%20Moran%20of%20Kansas%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0have%20signed%20on%20as%20co-sponsors%20to%20the%20bill.%20Republican%20Rep.%20Don%20Bacon%20has%20also%20said%20he'll%20introduce%20a%20companion%20House%20bill%20with%20similar%20provisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20four%20political%20scientists%20who%20each%20said%20that%2C%20while%20the%20bills%20proposed%20by%20the%20Republican%20lawmakers%20represent%20the%20first%20time%20some%20members%20of%20the%20president's%20party%20have%20split%20with%20him%20publicly%20since%20the%20election%2C%20the%20proposals%20are%20largely%20symbolic%20objections%20and%20are%20all%20but%20guaranteed%20not%20to%20pass%20because%2C%20even%20with%20the%20support%20of%20Democratic%20lawmakers%2C%20the%20bills%20simply%20won't%20have%20enough%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCongress%20has%20the%20ability%2C%20but%20Congress%2C%20as%20it's%20currently%20constituted%2C%20does%20not%20have%20the%20will%2C%26quot%3B%20Justin%20Crowe%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20Williams%20College%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20virtually%20no%20chance%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20near%20term.%20Were%20we%20to%20be%20in%20a%20fuller-blown%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-cuban-buy-lots-consumables-now-after-trump-tariff-rollout-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20we%20had%20some%20kind%20of%20economic%20downturn%20of%20a%20serious%20magnitude%20over%20the%20next%20number%20of%20months%2C%20potentially%2C%20you%20could%20see%20Congress%20trying%20to%20step%20in.%20But%20in%20the%20near%20term%2C%20that%20seems%20remarkably%2C%20vanishingly%20unlikely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Buchler%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20Case%20Western%20Reserve%20University%2C%20told%20BI%20that%2C%20technically%2C%20the%20proposed%20bills%20shouldn't%20even%20be%20necessary%20since%20the%20Constitution%20grants%20Congress%20the%20exclusive%20power%20to%20levy%20tariffs%20and%20duties.%20However%2C%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20lawmakers%20have%20taken%20a%20less%20active%20role%20in%20doing%20so%2C%20instead%20allowing%20the%20executive%20branch%20to%20execute%20tariff%20policies%20within%20the%20guidelines%20defined%20by%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220301cc07-5c38-4205-bf4c-27fe88ed1c60%5C%22%3ECongress%20won't%20claw%20back%20its%20trade%20power%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20different%20statutes%20exist%20to%20control%20how%20the%20president%20can%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftariffs-what-to-buy-before-price-increases-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Only%20three%20carve-outs%20exist%20to%20allow%20the%20president%20to%20impose%20tariffs%20without%20a%20congressional%20investigation.%20Still%2C%20only%20one%20has%20ever%20been%20used%3A%20the%20International%20Emergency%20Economic%20Powers%20Act%20of%201977%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20president%20to%20declare%20an%20emergency%20under%20the%20National%20Emergency%20Act%20to%20regulate%20or%20prohibit%20imports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20cited%20that%20power%20on%20Wednesday%20when%20he%20announced%20sweeping%2010%25%20tariffs%20on%20goods%20imported%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-canada-mexico-missing-from-donald-trump-reciprocal-tariff-chart-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealmost%20every%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20the%20United%20States%20and%20even%20higher%20tariffs%20for%2060%20trading%20partners%20with%20a%20persistent%20trade%20deficit%20with%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconstitutioncenter.org%2Fblog%2Fhow-congress-delegates-its-tariff-powers-to-the-president%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Constitution%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20other%20two%20presidential%20tariff%20carve-outs%2C%20which%20have%20never%20been%20used%2C%20stem%20from%20the%20Trade%20Act%20of%201974%20and%20the%20Tariff%20Act%20of%201930.%20Portions%20of%20these%20laws%20allow%20the%20president%20to%20enact%20temporary%20tariffs%20to%20address%20balance-of-payments%20deficits%20and%20tariffs%20on%20goods%20from%20foreign%20countries%20that%20discriminate%20against%20US%20commerce%20in%20certain%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20political%20scientists%20told%20Business%20Insider%20not%20to%20expect%20Congress%20to%20try%20to%20claw%20back%20its%20trade%20power%20in%20any%20real%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20this%20weird%20position%20where%2C%20constitutionally%2C%20no%20legislation%20should%20be%20necessary%20because%20what%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20doing%20is%20so%20far%20beyond%20the%20bounds%20of%20what%20the%20Constitution%20permits%20that%20nothing%20should%20be%20happening%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Buchler%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20courts%20aren't%20going%20to%20stop%20him%2C