city-dining-rent-costs-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMichelin%20star%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20it%20has%20held%20onto%20since%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Zhang%20expects%20the%20New%20York%20branch%20to%20get%20even%20greater%20plaudits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChinese%20immigrants%20are%20better%20educated%20and%20wealthier%20now.%20We%20crave%20for%20a%20better%20presentation%20of%20our%20own%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zhang.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20best%20time%20for%20food%20brands%20in%20China%20to%20expand%20overseas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20some%20Chinese%20fine-dining%20restaurants%20in%20the%20US%20run%20by%20Chinese%20Americans%2C%20the%20new%20wave%20brings%20some%20of%20the%20best-known%20restaurant%20brands%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20timing%20is%20made%20more%20urgent%20by%20China's%20recent%20economic%20troubles.%20The%20Chinese%20government%20says%20the%20revenue%20of%20the%20food%20and%20beverage%20industry%20in%20the%20country%20increased%20just%205.3%25%20in%202024%2C%20a%20nosedive%20from%20the%2020.4%25%20increase%20in%202023%2C%20and%20the%20smallest%20growth%20in%20a%20decade%20excluding%20the%20pandemic%20years.%20An%20industry%20report%20on%2022%20publicly%20listed%20Chinese%20food%20and%20beverage%20companies%20found%20that%2068%25%20saw%20their%20profits%20decline%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20last%20year.%20Close%20to%203%20million%20restaurants%20and%20caf%C3%A9s%20in%20China%20shut%20down%20for%20good%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChinese%20food%20brands'%20moves%20to%20open%20overseas%20%E2%80%94%20which%20had%20been%20increasing%20modestly%20since%20the%201980s%20%E2%80%94%20have%20rapidly%20accelerated.%20Hongcan%20Industry%20Research%20Institute%2C%20a%20Chinese%20group%20that%20studies%20the%20restaurant%20industry%2C%20released%20a%20report%20in%20September%20that%20found%20more%20than%20100%20Chinese%20food%20and%20beverage%20brands%20have%20moved%20into%20more%20than%20180%20countries%2C%20now%20running%20700%2C000%20locations%20outside%20China%20%E2%80%94%20a%20200%2C000%20increase%20since%202016.%20The%20Chinese%20government%20has%20spurred%20on%20the%20expansion%2C%20issuing%20two%20directives%20last%20year%20for%20Chinese%20food%20and%20beverage%20brands%20to%20%26quot%3Bgo%20overseas%26quot%3B%20to%20help%20%26quot%3Bimprove%20the%20international%20influence%20of%20Chinese%20cuisine%20culture.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlmost%20all%20the%20major%20food%20and%20beverage%20brands%20you%20see%20in%20China%20are%20considering%20coming%20to%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Beichen%20Hu%2C%20a%20restaurant%20investor%20and%20the%20director%20of%20the%20North%20America%20Asian%20Food%20Industry%20Association.%20%26quot%3BA%20popular%20catchphrase%20circulating%20broadly%20in%20the%20food%20industry%20in%20China%20is%20'to%20go%20overseas%20or%20to%20die.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20market%20certainly%20looks%20appealing.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurants-america-eating-out-crisis-your-fault-labor-shortage-tipping-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20service%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20reached%20over%20%241%20trillion%20in%20sales%20last%20year%2C%20with%20%241.5%20trillion%20projected%20in%202025.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frestaurant.org%2Fresearch-and-media%2Fmedia%2Fpress-releases%2Frestaurant-industry-poised-for-growth-in-2025-industry-expected-to-employ-15-9-million-people-and-r%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20National%20Restaurant%20Association%20found%20that%2080%25%20of%20restaurant%20operators%20in%20the%20US%20expect%20their%20sales%20this%20year%20to%20be%20the%20same%20or%20higher%20than%20last%20year's.%20An%20analysis%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ibisworld.com%2Funited-states%2Findustry%2Fchinese-restaurants%2F4304%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIBISWorld%3C%2Fa%3E%20predicted%20a%20promising%20market%20for%20Chinese%20restaurants%20in%20the%20US%20through%202030%20as%20the%20demand%20for%20Chinese%20food%20among%20households%20with%20annual%20income%20above%20%24100%2C000%20is%20expected%20to%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20as%20much%20of%20a%20setback%20as%20it%20was%2C%20the%20pandemic%20also%20offered%20a%20rare%20opportunity.%20%26quot%3BMany%20prime%20locations%20in%20coveted%20places%20like%20Manhattan%20are%20vacant%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20that%20opens%20the%20market%20for%20brands%20from%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tom%20Chen%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Kepler%20Mission%20Design%20Group%2C%20a%20design%20and%20branding%20company%20that's%20helped%20food%20and%20beverage%20chains%20from%20China%20open%20in%20the%20US.%20Leading%20Chinese%20brands%20have%20snatched%20up%20space%20in%20competitive%20areas%20like%20Fifth%20Avenue%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmidtown-manhattan-downtown-crisis-office-apocalypse-urban-doom-loop-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETimes%20Square%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20New%20York%20and%20Beverly%20Hills%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20brands%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20just%20another%20Chinese%20restaurant%20in%20the%20US%3B%20they%20want%20the%20esteem%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chao%20Wang%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20rice-noodle%20shop%20Hunan%20Slurp%20in%20New%20York's%20East%20Village.%20He's%20helping%20restaurants%20from%20Hunan%20province%2C%20where%20he's%20from%2C%20to%20open%20in%20the%20US.%20%26quot%3BTo%20have%20a%20store%20in%20Manhattan%20is%20like%20erecting%20a%20flag%20on%20the%20moon.%20It's%20worth%20it%20even%20if%20you%20don't%20make%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20cuisine%20push%20from%20China%20may%20seem%20counterintuitive.%20The%20tension%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%2C%20especially%20Washington's%20restrictions%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-details-when-how-legal-cases-trump-options%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20tech%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20has%20created%20a%20palpable%20chilling%20effect.%20Figures%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aei.org%2Fmultimedia%2Fchinese-investments-us-handout%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforeign%20investment%20from%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20vary%20significantly%2C%20but%20they%20all%20show%20a%20steep%20drop%20in%20Chinese%20investment%20into%20the%20US%20in%20the%20last%20several%20years.%20The%20most%20recent%20annual%20survey%20by%20the%20China%20General%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20%E2%80%94%20USA%20found%20that%20in%202023%2C%20more%20than%2060%25%20of%20Chinese%20companies%20in%20the%20US%20complained%20about%20the%20deteriorating%20business%20environment%20and%2022%25%20had%20reduced%20investment%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-china-biggest-geopolitical-risk-in-the-world-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egeopolitical%20risks%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20not%20top%20of%20mind%20for%20most%20eateries.%20%26quot%3BThe%20US%20is%20still%20a%20pro-business%20country.%20And%20we%20sell%20consumer%20products%2C%20not%20computer%20chips%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Amanda%20Wang%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20Ningji%2C%20the%20leading%20Chinese%20chain%20of%20lemon-based%20teas%2C%20with%20more%20than%203%2C000%20stores%20in%20China.%20Its%20first%20overseas%20outlet%20is%20opening%20in%20mid-April%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20with%20a%20product%20line%20customized%20for%20American%20consumers%20called%20bobobaba.%20And%20the%20company%20is%20already%20looking%20for%20more%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWang%20said%20the%20biggest%20cultural%20shock%20for%20her%20is%20the%20time%20it%20takes%20to%20open%20a%20store%20in%20the%20US.%20Ningji%20decided%20to%20take%20over%20the%20fully%20functioning%20venue%20of%20a%20shuttered%20beverage%20store%20in%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20suburb%20of%20Glendale%20last%20November%2C%20but%20as%20of%20early%20February%2C%20Wang%20was%20still%20waiting%20for%20the%20license%20to%20be%20approved%20to%20start%20the%20renovation.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20speechless%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wang.%20%26quot%3BWe%20open%20a%20new%20store%20on%20average%20in%2020%20days%20in%20China.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWang%20was%20also%20confused%20by%20a%20recent%20street%20encounter.%20Two%20days%20before%20the%20new%20year%2C%20on%20her%20way%20to%20the%20supermarket%2C%20a%20stranger%20yelled%20at%20her%20to%20%26quot%3Bgo%20back%20to%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20blamed%20her%20for%20stealing%20jobs%20in%20the%20US.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20understand%20why%20he%20thought%20I%20stole%20his%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wang.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20here%20to%20create%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20hostility%20isn't%20exactly%20rare.%20A%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20survey%20from%20May%20found%20that%20eight%20in%2010%20Americans%20have%20negative%20views%20about%20China%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D6cd45e65d84e4697e7197a8e6355d2725ab13bc68080d2540154409a0cfffc8e%26postID%3D67e55104e2041f80933cf85e%26postSlug%3Dchina-restaurants-food-chains-coming-us-geopolitical-trade-war-backlash-2025-4%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41562-022-01493-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20researchers%20from%20Boston%20College%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20found%20that%20Asian%20restaurants%20in%20the%20US%20lost%20%247.4%20billion%20in%20revenue%20in%202020%20because%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-chinatown-wo-hop-owner-on-business-anti-asian-discrimination-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanti-Chinese%20sentiment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20helped%20stoke%20by%20calling%20COVID-19%20the%20%26quot%3BChina%20virus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrump%20likes%20to%20stir%20racial%20antagonism%2C%26quot%3B%20Chao%20Wang%20of%20Hunan%20Slurp%20said.%20The%20window%20of%20a%20noodle%20shop%20Wang%20owned%20in%20Long%20Island%20City%2C%20New%20York%2C%20was%20smashed%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20he%20attributed%20it%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinatown-partnership-hate-crimes-racism-coronavirus-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanti-Asian%20hate%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYong%20Zhao%2C%20the%20cofounder%20and%20chief%20executive%20of%20the%20American%20food%20chains%20Junzi%20Kitchen%20and%20Nice%20Day%2C%20had%20a%20disturbing%20moment%20a%20few%20months%20ago%20with%20a%20customer%20at%20his%20store%20in%20Long%20Island.%20%26quot%3BI%20told%20him%20we%20are%20going%20to%20bring%20organic%20mushrooms%20from%20a%20local%20farm%20into%20our%20recipes%2C%20and%20he%20said%2C%20'Oh%2C%20is%20the%20farm%20owned%20by%20the%20CCP%3F'%26quot%3B%20said%20Zhao.%20The%20customer%20was%20referring%20to%20the%20rising%20concern%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-michigan-towns-war-over-a-chinese-owned-battery-plant-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20Communist%20Party%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20spying%20on%20the%20US%20from%20farmlands%20purchased%20by%20Chinese%20entities.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20were%20white%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20he'd%20have%20asked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Zhao%2C%20a%20Yale-educated%20environmental%20scientist%20turned%20restaurateur%2C%20had%20formed%20a%20network%20of%20young%20Chinese%20restaurant%20operators%20in%20the%20US%20with%20a%20mission%20to%20%26quot%3Btell%20the%20stories%20of%20Chinese%20cuisine.%26quot%3B%20But%20he%20said%20since%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-china-trump-trade-war-tariffs-retaliation-counter-measures-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20began%20in%202018%2C%20American%20media%20has%20much%20less%20coverage%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-work-culture-differences-west-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20lifestyle%2C%20and%20Americans%20seem%20less%20interested%20in%20Chinese%20culture.%20%26quot%3BSay%2C%20you%20want%20to%20highlight%20the%20history%20of%20a%20traditional%20dish%20from%20Chengdu%2C%20but%20many%20people%20here%20don't%20know%20where%20Chengdu%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zhao%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20southwestern%20Chinese%20city%20that%20is%20known%20for%20mapo%20tofu%20and%20kung%20pao%20chicken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20some%20industry%20people%20I%20spoke%20with%2C%20Chinese%20food%20companies%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20caught%20up%20in%20geopolitical%20wrangling%20than%2C%20say%2C%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20but%20their%20biggest%20risk%20factor%20may%20be%20their%20own%20growth.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20an%20industry%20that%20is%20safe%20until%20Chinese%20companies%20start%20to%20win%2C%20and%20then%20they're%20not%20safe%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chris%20Pereira%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20iMpact%2C%20a%20New%20York-based%20consulting%20firm%20that%20has%20helped%20hundreds%20of%20Chinese%20enterprises%20enter%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20he%20founded%20iMpact%20in%202020%2C%20Pereira%20worked%20as%20an%20executive%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-chinese-telecoms-company-huawei-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHuawei%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Chinese%20tech%20conglomerate%20that%20was%20driven%20out%20of%20the%20US%20market%20over%20national%20security%20concerns.%20Having%20watched%20that%20play%20out%2C%20Pereira%20suggests%20big%20Chinese%20food%20chains%20find%20ways%20to%20share%20profits%20with%20American%20partners%20as%20a%20form%20of%20self-protection.%20For%20instance%2C%20he%20said%2C%20if%20Luckin%20Coffee%2C%20the%20Chinese%20coffeehouse%20behemoth%20with%20more%20than%2022%2C000%20locations%20in%20China%20that%20plans%20to%20come%20to%20the%20US%20this%20year%2C%20starts%20to%20steal%20market%20share%20from%20Starbucks%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20can%20bet%20the%20US%20government%20will%20find%20a%20way%20to%20talk%20about%20national%20security%20for%20coffee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20crowded%20back%20office%20at%20Quanjude's%20Manhattan%20site%2C%20Zhang%20has%20a%20more%20urgent%20challenge.%20The%20visa%20applications%20for%20the%20five%20chefs%20he%20plans%20to%20bring%20in%20from%20China%20are%20still%20pending.%20Since%20US-China%20relations%20started%20deteriorating%2C%20it's%20been%20harder%20to%20obtain%20visas%20for%20Chinese%20nationals%2C%20but%20Zhang%20says%20the%20Chinese-trained%20chefs%20are%20essential%20for%20the%20restaurant.%20%26quot%3BWe%20won't%20allow%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20food%20to%20suffer%20under%20untrained%20hands%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20If%20nothing%20else%20works%20out%2C%20he%20plans%20to%20bring%20Quanjude%20chefs%20from%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhang%20thinks%20his%20ducks%20could%20serve%20an%20important%20mission.%20%26quot%3BI%20believe%20food%20is%20the%20best%20bridge%20for%20divisions%20and%20it%20may%20help%20pull%20the%20US%20and%20China%20closer%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20pause%2C%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BExcept%20if%20there%20is%20a%20hot%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Beverything%20Chinese%20in%20the%20US%20would%20be%20doomed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Frong-xiaoqing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ERong%20Xiaoqing%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3Eis%20a%20New%20York-based%20award-winning%20journalist%20who%20has%20been%20writing%20about%20the%20Chinese%20community%20in%20the%20US%20since%202002.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdi