tte-is-the-biggest-victim-of-elon-musks-doge-cuts-in-the-consultancy-industry%2Farticleshow%2F120006760.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Deloitte%20has%20borne%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency's%20crackdown%2C%20losing%20124%20federal%20contracts%20since%20January%20and%20saving%20taxpayers%20an%20estimated%20%24371.8%20million.%20This%20represents%20more%20than%20double%20the%20cuts%20faced%20by%20any%20other%20consultancy%2C%20impacting%20key%20agencies%20and%20leading%20to%20potential%20layoffs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Can%20You%20Really%20Trust%20Trump's%20'Magic%20Potion'%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAnthony%20Scaramucci%2C%20a%20Wall%20Street%20stalwart%2C%20knows%20Donald%20Trump%20up%20close%20and%20personal.%20What%20stands%20out%20most%20to%20him%20is%20Trump's%20%E2%80%9Ccruel%E2%80%9D%20nature.%20Yet%2C%20as%20he%20repeats%20ad%20nauseam%20in%20his%20podcasts%2C%20Trump%20has%20incredibly%20sharp%20political%20instincts.%20According%20to%20Scaramucci%2C%20Trump%20always%20follows%20his%20gut%20-%20something%20instilled%20in%20him%20by%20his%20mentor%2C%20the%20ultra-aggressive%20New%20York%20lawyer%20Roy%20Cohn.%20And%20Scaramucci%20should%20know%20-%20he%20briefly%20served%20as%20White%20House%20Director%20of%20Communications%20under%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20as%20the%20world%20grapples%20with%20the%20fallout%20from%20Trump's%20April%202%20announcement%20of%20sweeping%20reciprocal%20tariffs%2C%20one%20has%20to%20wonder%3A%20are%20Trump's%20instincts%20right%20this%20time%3F%20Trump%20has%20dominated%20American%20politics%20for%20the%20better%20part%20of%20a%20decade%2C%20but%20these%20new%20tariffs%20fly%20in%20the%20face%20of%20economic%2C%20business%2C%20and%20political%20logic.%20It's%20hard%20to%20see%20how%20they%20serve%20his%20political%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsider%20the%20context%20of%20Trump's%20self-declared%20%E2%80%9CLiberation%20Day%E2%80%9D.%20Here's%20what%20veteran%20Republican%20strategist%20Karl%20Rove%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20April%203%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20problem%20for%20Republicans%20is%20that%20Mr.%20Trump%20was%20elected%20to%20stop%20inflation.%20A%20March%2028%20%3Cem%3ECBS%20News%3C%2Fem%3E%20poll%20found%20that%2064%25%20of%20Americans%20already%20think%20Mr.%20Trump%20isn't%20focused%20enough%20on%20'lowering%20prices'%2C%20while%2055%25%20say%20he's%20focused%20too%20much%20on%20raising%20tariffs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERove%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BMost%20Americans%20believe%20Mr.%20Trump's%20economic%20policies%20are%20either%20making%20them%20'financially%20worse%20off'%20(42%25)%20or%20'about%20the%20same'%20(35%25).%20Fifty%20two%20percent%20feel%20his%20policies%20are%20making%20food%20and%20groceries%20prices%20go%20up%2C%20only%2022%25%20say%20go%20down.%20Fifty-one%20percent%20think%20his%20policies%20are%20making%20the%20stock%20market%20fall%2C%20compared%20with%2023%25%20saying%20his%20policies%20are%20making%20it%20rise.%20Only%2033%25%20believe%20his%20'policies%20are%20making%20the%20US%20job%20market'%20create%20jobs%2C%20while%2048%25%20say%20they%20are%20making%20it%20'lose%20jobs'...Americans%20are%20skittish%20about%20tariffs%3A%2056%25%20oppose%20them%2C%20with%2072%25%20believing%20they'll%20raise%20prices%20in%20the%20short%20run%20compared%20to%205%25%20who%20think%20they'll%20reduce%20prices.%20Over%20the%20long%20term%2C%20only%2029%25%20say%20they'll%20lower%20prices.%20They'll%20certainly%20remember%20Mr.%20Trump%20saying%20he%20'couldn't%20care%20less'%20if%20US%20automakers%20raised%20prices%20because%20they%20had%20to%20pay%20more%20for%20imported%20parts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEstimates%20suggest%20that%20under%20Trump's%20tariff%20regime%2C%20new%20car%20prices%20could%20rise%20anywhere%20from%20%242%2C500%20to%20%2420%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPopular%20Opinion%20Turning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there's%20the%20potential%20impact%20on%20American%20farmers%E2%80%94numerically%20small%20but%20among%20Trump's%20most%20loyal%20voters.%20In%20the%20last%20election%2C%20Trump%20won%20nearly%2078%25%20of%20the%20vote%20in%20the%20444%20counties%20where%20farming%20dominates.%20As%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Atlantic%3C%2Fem%3E%20put%20it%2C%20%E2%80%9CTariffs%20will%20indeed%20hurt%20farmers%20badly.%20Farm%20costs%20will%20rise.%20Farm%20incomes%20will%20drop.%20Under%20Trump's%20tariffs%2C%20farmers%20will%20pay%20more%20for%20fertilizer.%20They%20will%20pay%20more%20for%20farm%20equipment.%20They%20will%20pay%20more%20for%20the%20fuel%20to%20ship%20their%20products%20to%20market.%20When%20foreign%20countries%20retaliate%2C%20raising%20their%20own%20tariff%20barriers%2C%20American%20farmers%20will%20lose%20export%20markets.%20Their%20domestic%20sales%20will%20come%20under%20pressure%20too%2C%20because%20tariffs%20will%20shrink%20America%20disposable%20incomes%3A%20Consumers%20will%20have%20to%20cut%20back%20everywhere%2C%20including%20at%20the%20grocery%20store.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20long%20believed%20that%20both%20allies%20and%20adversaries%20have%20exploited%20the%20post-World%20War%20II%20trade%20regime%20-%20where%20the%20US%20promoted%20global%20prosperity%20with%20low%20import%20tariffs%20while%20enduring%20higher%20tariffs%20on%20its%20exports%20-%20to%20enrich%20themselves%20at%20America's%20expense.%20As%20two%20economists%20recently%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EForeign%20Affairs%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CTrump%20possesses%20few%20consistent%20political%20ideologies%20but%20has%20promoted%20tariffs%20since%20the%201980s%20as%20a%20means%20to%20reduce%20trade%20deficits%20and%20spur%20US%20manufacturing%2C%20dismissing%20economists'%20warnings%20that%20they%20would%20raise%20prices%20and%20potentially%20stagnate%20the%20U.S.%20economy.%E2%80%9D%20'Make%20them%20pay%20for%20the%20privilege%20of%20selling%20to%20or%20being%20defended%20by%20the%20US'%20-%20whether%20NATO%2C%20Japan%2C%20or%20South%20Korea%20-%20is%20a%20core%20Trump%20and%20MAGA%20tenet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EJust%20'A%20Little%20Disturbance'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Trump%20sees%20tariffs%20as%20a%20cure-all%20for%20America's%20economic%20woes.%20Short-term%20pain%20-%20what%20Trump%20calls%20%E2%80%9Ca%20little%20disturbance%E2%80%9D%20-%20is%20a%20price%20he%20seems%20willing%20to%20pay%20to%20fulfill%20this%20vision.%20He%20argues%20that%20the%20tariffs%20will%20restore%20American%20manufacturing%20and%20generate%20%E2%80%9Ctrillions%20and%20trillions%20of%20dollars%E2%80%9D%20in%20government%20revenue%2C%20which%20could%20be%20used%20to%20lower%20taxes%20and%20pay%20down%20the%20national%20debt.%20According%20to%20his%20team's%20projections%2C%20the%20announced%20tariffs%20would%20generate%20%246%20trillion%20over%20a%20decade.%20Just%20the%20flat%2010%25%20tariff%20on%20all%20imports%2C%20they%20say%2C%20would%20alone%20create%202.8%20million%20jobs%20by%20reshoring%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20are%20signs%2C%20Trump's%20team%20claims%2C%20that%20his%20%E2%80%9CAmerica%20First%E2%80%9D%20trade%20policy%20is%20already%20yielding%20results%20-%20namely%20increased%20domestic%20investment%20and%20early%20signs%20of%20reshoring.%20According%20to%20the%20White%20House%20press%20site%2C%20some%20two%20dozen%20post-inauguration%20investment%20decisions%20have%20been%20made%20by%20U.S.%20and%20global%20giants%20across%20sectors%20including%20IT%2C%20AI%2C%20automobiles%2C%20and%20pharmaceuticals.%20These%20commitments%20total%20well%20over%20%241%20trillion%2C%20including%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EApple%3A%20%24500%20billion%3B%2020%2C000%20jobs%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAI%20Infrastructure%3A%20%24500%20billion%20in%20private%20investment%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENvidia%3A%20Hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20U.S.%20investment%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETSMC%3A%20%24100%20billion%20investment%20in%20a%20new%20facility%20by%20the%20Taiwanese%20semiconductor%20giant%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Trump%20boasted%20to%20a%20group%20of%20blue-collar%20workers%3A%20%E2%80%9CEmpty%2C%20dead%20sites%2C%20factories%20that%20are%20falling%20down%E2%80%A6will%20be%20knocked%20down%2C%20and%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20brand%20new%20factories%20built%20in%20their%20place.%20We're%20going%20to%20be%20an%20entirely%20different%20country.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0He%20added%20the%20day%20after%20announcing%20the%20tariffs%3A%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3EEvery%20country's%20called%20us.%20That's%20the%20beauty%20of%20what%20we%20do.%20We're%20in%20the%20driver's%20seat.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20team%20hopes%20that%20the%20disruptive%20effects%20of%20tariffs%2C%20deportations%2C%20and%20spending%20cuts%20will%20fade%2C%20making%20way%20for%20the%20expected%20benefits%3A%20reshoring%2C%20cheaper%20energy%2C%20and%20lower%20taxes.%20%E2%80%9CLet%20Donald%20Trump%20run%20the%20global%20economy%2C%E2%80%9D%20Commerce%20Secretary%20Howard%20Lutnick%20told%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20knows%20what%20he's%20doing.%20He's%20been%20talking%20about%20it%20for%2035%20years.%20You've%20got%20to%20trust%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20the%20White%20House.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAgainst%20Post-WW2%20Tenets%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20can%20you%20trust%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Trump%20Tariff%20Magic%20Potion%E2%80%9D%20when%20it%20appears%20to%20ignore%20Economics%20101%3F%20Can%20you%2C%20when%20it%20disregards%20the%20structural%20realities%20of%20both%20the%20US%20and%20global%20economies%3F%20Can%20you%2C%20when%20nearly%20a%20century%20of%20reduced%20tariffs%20-%20especially%20in%20the%20post-World%20War%20II%20era%20under%20GATT%20and%20later%20the%20WTO%20-%20has%20proven%20that%20a%20liberal%20trade%20regime%20is%20essential%20for%20embedding%20competitiveness%20and%20innovation%2C%20the%20twin%20engines%20of%20productivity%2C%20which%20is%20the%20surest%20path%20to%20long-term%20growth%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEconomists%20argue%20that%20the%20US%20trade%20deficit%20is%20structural%20and%20inevitable%3A%20it%20stems%20from%20a%20low%20national%20savings%20rate%20paired%20with%20high%20consumption%20and%20investment.%20Foreign%20goods%20and%20capital%20are%20the%20economy's%20lifeblood.%20Yes%2C%20the%20US%20imports%20more%20goods%20than%20it%20exports%20-%20but%20it%20exports%20far%20more%20services%20than%20it%20imports.%20More%20than%2040%25%20of%20US%20imports%20are%20components%20for%20domestic%20production.%20Tariffs%20on%20them%20simply%20raise%20production%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobalisation%20has%20cost%20the%20US%20over%20five%20million%20manufacturing%20jobs%2C%20but%20thanks%20to%20its%20comparative%20advantage%20in%20tech-driven%20services%20-%20think%20Apple%20and%20Nvidia%20-%20the%20US%20growth%20rate%20has%20consistently%20outperformed%20other%20Western%20economies.%20The%20US%20still%20generates%20about%2025%25%20of%20global%20GDP.%20Many%20American%20companies%20have%20invested%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20in%20global%20supply%20chains%20that%20cannot%20easily%20be%20unwound.%20Roughly%2041%25%20of%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20revenues%20come%20from%20overseas.%20And%20US%20manufacturing%2C%20focused%20as%20it%20is%20on%20high-tech%20products%2C%20lacks%20domestic%20sources%20for%20many%20basic%20materials%20and%20components.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20in%20the%20US%20economy%20from%20manufacturing%20to%20services%20tells%20a%20clear%20story.%20Over%20the%20past%2030%20years%2C%20manufacturing's%20share%20of%20GDP%20has%20fallen%20from%2016%25%20to%2010%25%2C%20with%20employment%20dropping%20from%20nearly%2018%20million%20to%2010%20million%20in%20a%20168%20million-strong%20workforce.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20services%20sector%20has%20grown%20dramatically%3A%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20has%20risen%20from%2084%20million%20to%20133%20million%2C%20jobs%20now%20account%20for%2080%25%20of%20employment%20(up%20from%2070%25)%2C%20and%20the%20sector's%20GDP%20share%20has%20climbed%20from%2070%25%20to%2075%25.%20Over%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20US%20service%20exports%20have%20grown%20at%20a%20compound%20annual%20growth%20rate%20of%20nearly%204%25%2C%20amounting%20to%20a%20total%20increase%20of%20almost%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Flat-Out%20Nonsense'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fem%3E%20editorialised%20the%20day%20after%20the%20tariff%20announcement%3A%20%E2%80%9CMr.%20Trump%20is%20making%20a%20deliberate%20decision%20to%20transfer%20wealth%20from%20consumers%20to%20businesses%20and%20workers%20protected%20from%20competition%20behind%20high%20tariff%20walls.%20Over%20time%2C%20this%20will%20mean%20the%20gradual%20erosion%20of%20US%20competitiveness.%20Tariffs%20that%20blunt%20competition%20invite%20monopoly%20profits%20while%20reducing%20the%20need%20to%20innovate.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Economist%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20even%20more%20blunt%3A%20%E2%80%9COn%20economics%2C%20Mr%20Trump's%20assertions%20are%20flat-out%20nonsense.%20The%20president%20says%20tariffs%20are%20needed%20to%20close%20America's%20trade%20deficit%2C%20which%20he%20sees%20as%20a%20transfer%20of%20wealth%20to%20foreigners.%20Yet%20as%20any%20of%20the%20president's%20economists%20could%20have%20told%20him%2C%20this%20long-running%20reality%20has%20not%20stopped%20its%20economy%20from%20outpacing%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20G7%20for%20over%20three%20decades.%20Insisting%20on%20balanced%20trade%20with%20every%20trading%20partner%20individually%20is%20bonkers%20-%20like%20suggesting%20that%20Texas%20would%20be%20richer%20if%20it%20insisted%20on%20balanced%20trade%20with%20each%20of%20the%20other%2049%20states%2C%20or%20asking%20a%20company%20to%20ensure%20that%20each%20of%20its%20suppliers%20is%20also%20a%20customer.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20recently%2C%20the%20weighted%20average%20tariff%20rate%20on%20US%20imports%20stood%20at%20just%202%25.%20Under%20Trump's%20new%20tariff%20regime%20-%20dubbed%20the%20'Trump%20Potion'%20-%20that%20figure%20is%20projected%20to%20surge%20to%20somewhere%20between%2024%25%20and%2027%25.%20If%20that%20seems%20implausibly%20high%20and%20suggests%20this%20might%20be%20merely%20an%20opening%20gambit%20in%20broader%20negotiations%2C%20there's%20evidence%20from%20within%20the%20Trump%20camp%20that%20it%20may%20indeed%20be%20just%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20The%20%3Cem%3ENew%20Yorker%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20paper%20published%20immediately%20after%20last%20year's%20election%2C%20Stephen%20Miran%20-%20a%20Harvard-trained%20economist%20who%20was%20then%20working%20at%20a%20hedge%20fund%20and%20is%20now%20chair%20of%20the%20Council%20of%20Economic%20Advisers%20-%20tied%20Trump's%20tariff%20proposals%20to%20his%20America%20First%20foreign%20policy.%20He%20suggested%20they%20could%20be%20part%20of%20a%20grand%20strategy%20to%20reduce%20the%20US%20trade%20deficit%20while%20pressuring%20allies%20to%20share%20the%20burden%20of%20America's%20defense%20commitments%20and%20national%20debt.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMiran%20argued%20that%20the%20tariffs%20would%20primarily%20serve%20as%20bargaining%20chips%2C%20giving%20Trump%20leverage%20to%20push%20for%20a%20devaluation%20of%20the%20dollar%20-%20making%20US%20exports%20more%20competitive%20-%20and%20for%20a%20refinancing%20of%20the%20national%20debt.%20His%20proposed%20mechanism%3A%20foreign%20holders%20of%20U.S.%20Treasuries%20(of%20which%20there%20are%20many)%20would%20exchange%20them%20for%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20security%20-%20century-long%20bonds%20carrying%20extremely%20low%20interest%20rates%20-%20thereby%20making%20it%20cheaper%20for%20the%20US%20government%20to%20borrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20would%20other%20countries%20accept%20such%20a%20lopsided%20deal%3F%20Miran%20didn't%20fully%20explain%2C%20but%20the%20implication%20was%20clear%3A%20they%20wouldn't%20have%20much%20choice%20if%20they%20wanted%20continued%20access%20to%20the%20US%20market%20and%20its%20military%20protection.%20Miran%20even%20dubbed%20this%20potential%20restructuring%20of%20the%20global%20trade%20system%20the%20%26quot%3BMar-a-Lago%20Accord%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20Trump%20Overestimating%20US%20Influence%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20strategy%20appears%20to%20rest%20on%20an%20overestimation%20of%20US%20influence%20in%20global%20trade.%20While%20America%20dominates%20global%20finance%20and%20military%20spending%2C%20its%20share%20of%20global%20imports%20is%20around%2015%25.%20As%20the%20US%20weakens%20the%20rule-based%20WTO%20system%2C%20a%20complex%20and%20expanding%20web%20of%20bilateral%20and%20regional%20trade%20agreements%20is%20reshaping%20global%20commerce.%20These%20deals%20-%20many%20centered%20around%20the%20EU%2C%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20and%20Gulf%20regions%20-%20are%20increasingly%20weighted%20toward%20the%20world's%20fastest-growing%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20EU%2C%20the%2012%20members%20of%20the%20Comprehensive%20and%20Progressive%20Agreement%20for%20Trans-Pacific%20Partnership%20(CPTPP)%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20and%20small%20but%20open%20economies%20like%20Norway%20together%20account%20for%2034%25%20of%20global%20import%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWarning%20Lights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20warning%20lights%20are%20flashing%20for%20Trump%20across%20key%20political%20and%20economic%20indicators.%20His%20approval%20rating%20on%20Real%20Clear%20Politics%20has%20dropped%20by%20three%20points%20since%20January%2C%20while%20his%20disapproval%20rating%20has%20jumped%20by%20five.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinancial%20markets%20have%20reacted%20sharply.%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20down%20nearly%2010%25%20since%20its%20February%20peak.%20On%20the%20day%20the%20tariffs%20were%20announced%2C%20the%20market%20shed%20%243.1%20trillion%2C%20a%204.8%25%20drop.%20Inflation%2C%20which%20had%20been%20trending%20down%20to%202%25%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20rebound%20to%204%25.%20Moody's%20has%20warned%20that%20a%20recession%20is%20inevitable%20if%20the%20proposed%20trade%20policies%20are%20fully%20implemented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20political%20ground%20is%20shifting.%20On%20the%20day%20the%20tariffs%20were%20announced%2C%20a%20high-profile%20Republican%20nominee%20lost%20a%20Wisconsin%20Supreme%20Court%20race%20to%20a%20liberal%20challenger%20-%20despite%20Elon%20Musk%20personally%20investing%20%2425%20million%20and%20his%20own%20clout%20in%20the%20contest.%20While%20Republican%20turnout%20rose%2C%20even%20more%20Democrats%20showed%20up%20to%20vote.%20That%20same%20day%2C%20four%20GOP%20Senators%20broke%20ranks%2C%20joining%20Democrats%20to%20pass%20a%20resolution%20aimed%20at%20overturning%20Trump's%2025%25%20tariff%20on%20Canadian%20imports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20faces%20a%20major%20short-term%20political%20challenge%3A%20the%20tariffs%20are%20likely%20to%20hurt%20two%20key%20constituencies%20of%20the%20GOP%20-%20business%20leaders%20and%20working-class%20MAGA%20voters.%20But%20perhaps%20Trump%20understands%20these%20groups%20better%20than%20we%20think.%20Business%20leaders%20abhor%20uncertainty%2C%20yes%2C%20but%20they%20may%20tolerate%20it%20if%20rewarded%20with%20deregulation%20and%20tax%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20MAGA%20faithful%3F%20A%20revealing%20vignette%20from%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20captured%20the%20sentiment%20at%20the%20Rose%20Garden%20tariff%20announcement.%20After%20Trump%20returned%20to%20the%20White%20House%2C%20a%20few%20men%20in%20hard%20hats%20and%20reflective%20vests%20lingered%20among%20cabinet%20secretaries%20and%20lawmakers%2C%20stunned%20they%20had%20been%20invited%20at%20all.%20%E2%80%9CIt's%20just%20so%20great%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Danny%20Hess%2C%20a%2062-year-old%20coal%20miner%20from%20Russell%20County%2C%20Virginia.%20But%20what%20if%20critics%20are%20right%2C%20and%20the%20tariffs%20plunge%20the%20country%20into%20recession%3F%20%E2%80%9CWe'll%20just%20have%20to%20wait%20and%20see%2C%E2%80%9D%20Hess%20shrugged.%20Asked%20whether%20he%20was%20worried%2C%20he%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CNot%20really%E2%80%94because%20things%20have%20been%20so%20disastrous%20for%20so%20long%20anyway.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Ajay%20Kumar%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist.%20He%20is%20former%20Managing%20Editor%2C%20Business%20Standard%2C%20and%20former%20Executive%20Editor%2C%20The%20Economic%20Times.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743837420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F5h5bn5sc_donald-trump-tariffs-announcement-afp_625x300_03_April_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcan-you-really-trust-trumps-magic-potion-8092399%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump%20faces%20a%20major%20short-term%20political%20challenge%3A%20the%20tariffs%20are%20likely%20to%20hurt%20two%20key%20constituencies%20of%20the%20GOP%20-%20business%20leaders%20and%20working-class%20MAGA%20voters.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meghalaya%2010th%20Board%20Result%202025%20Out%2C%20Massive%2031%25%20Jump%20In%20Pass%20Percentage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMBOSE%20SSLC%20Result%202025%20Out%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Meghalaya%20Board%20of%20School%20Education%20(MBOSE)%20has%20officially%20announced%20the%20results%20of%20the%20Secondary%20School%20Leaving%20Certificate%20(SSLC)%20Examination%202025.%20Students%20w