-catholic-priest-arul-carasala-shot-dead-in-kansas-1-charged-8092131%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Aurangzeb%2C%20The%20Ghosts%20Of%20History%2C%20And%20The%20Politics%20of%20Remembrance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20nation%2C%20India%20often%20finds%20itself%20in%20a%20tug-of-war%20between%20the%20grandeur%20of%20its%20aspirations%20and%20the%20ghosts%20of%20its%20past.%20One%20would%20imagine%20that%20a%20country%20poised%20as%20a%20global%20power%20-%20boasting%20nuclear%20capabilities%2C%20a%20pioneering%20space%20programme%2C%20a%20%26quot%3BTech%20Stack%26quot%3B%20that%20is%20the%20envy%20of%20the%20world%20and%20an%20ambitious%20bid%20for%20a%20permanent%20seat%20on%20the%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20-%20has%20moved%20beyond%20debates%20over%20a%20Mughal%20emperor%20who%20breathed%20his%20last%20more%20than%20300%20years%20ago.%20Yet%2C%20here%20we%20are%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20unrest%20in%20Nagpur%20over%20the%20Mughal%20Emperor%20Aurangzeb%20is%20one%20more%20reminder%20that%20in%20India%2C%20debates%20over%20history%20are%20not%20confined%20to%20the%20distant%20past%20alone.%20The%20turmoil%20underscores%20the%20enduring%20potency%20of%20history%20as%20a%20political%20tool.%20Clashes%20erupted%20after%20Hindu%20nationalist%20protesters%20allied%20with%20the%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20burned%20an%20effigy%20of%20Aurangzeb%2C%20the%20controversial%20Mughal%20emperor%20whose%20name%20evokes%20varying%20emotions%20across%20India's%20diverse%20spectrum.%20The%20protesters%20demanded%20the%20destruction%20of%20his%20unassuming%20grave%2C%20a%20move%20that%20enraged%20many%20Muslims%20and%20secular%20Hindus%20alike.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMatters%20That%20Still%20Matter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20does%20Aurangzeb%2C%20who%20ruled%20the%20Mughal%20Empire%20from%201658%20to%201707%2C%20continue%20to%20provoke%20such%20fervent%20reactions%20centuries%20after%20his%20demise%3F%20To%20his%20detractors%2C%20particularly%20within%20Hindu%20nationalist%20circles%2C%20Aurangzeb%20epitomises%20tyranny%20-%20accused%20of%20destroying%20temples%2C%20reimposing%20Islamic%20taxes%20on%20Hindus%2C%20executing%20Sikh%20spiritual%20leaders%2C%20and%20enforcing%20policies%20that%20suppressed%20Hindu%20traditions.%20To%20some%20Indian%20Muslims%2C%20however%2C%20he%20is%20remembered%20for%20his%20piety%20and%20military%20glory%2C%20having%20expanded%20the%20Mughal%20Empire%20to%20its%20zenith%2C%20encompassing%20regions%20from%20Kabul%20to%20Dhaka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20secular%20historians%2C%20the%20case%20against%20demonising%20Aurangzeb%20lies%20in%20context.%20He%20was%2C%20after%20all%2C%20a%20product%20of%20his%20time%2C%20when%20religious%20intolerance%20and%20political%20violence%20were%20established%20norms.%20His%20record%20includes%20grants%20to%20some%20Hindu%20temples%20alongside%20the%20destruction%20of%20others%20-%20a%20paradox%20often%20overlooked%20in%20the%20discourse.%20Yet%2C%20the%20argument%20that%20India%20needs%20to%20%26quot%3Bmove%20on%26quot%3B%20from%20Aurangzeb%20faces%20formidable%20resistance%20in%20a%20country%20grappling%20with%20its%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhereas%20conservatives%2C%20in%20the%20famous%20phrase%2C%20are%20%E2%80%98standing%20athwart%20history%2C%20yelling%20Stop'%2C%20our%20Hindutva%20nationalists%20are%20yelling%20%E2%80%98turn%20back!%20Reverse!'%20Their%20reinvention%20of%20history%20is%20not%20anchored%20in%20a%20reverence%20for%20the%20past%2C%20but%20in%20their%20desire%20to%20shape%20the%20present%20by%20reinventing%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistory%20As%20Politics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistory%20has%20often%20been%20contested%20terrain%20in%20India%2C%20but%20its%20revival%20in%20the%20context%20of%20twenty-first%20century%20politics%20is%20a%20sobering%20sign%20that%20the%20past%20continues%20to%20have%20a%20hold%20over%20the%20Hindutva%20movement%20in%20the%20present.%20While%20the%20Mughals%20are%20being%20demonised%20as%20a%20way%20of%20delegitimising%20Indian%20Muslims%20(who%20are%20stigmatised%20as%20%E2%80%98Babur%20ke%20aulad'%2C%20the%20sons%20of%20the%20invader%20Babur%20rather%20than%20of%20the%20Indian%20soil)%2C%20Hindutva%20zealots%20want%20to%20rebuild%20the%20most%20prominent%20of%20the%20Hindu%20temples%20the%20Mughals%20allegedly%20destroyed.%20And%20some%20in%20Nagpur%20want%20to%20destroy%20a%20simple%20grave%20because%20of%20what%20its%20contents%20represent%3A%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20humiliation%20of%20their%20ancestors%20centuries%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ideological%20battle%20unfolding%20today%20-%20whether%20over%20Aurangzeb%20or%20the%20broader%20legacy%20of%20Islamic%20rule%20-%20reflects%20the%20interplay%20between%20history%20and%20nationalism.%20The%20renaming%20of%20Aurangabad%20to%20Chhatrapati%20Sambhajinagar%20and%20the%20replacement%20of%20Aurangzeb%20Road%20in%20New%20Delhi%20with%20a%20more%20palatable%20alternative%20are%20not%20isolated%20incidents.%20They%20fit%20neatly%20into%20a%20broader%20campaign%20to%20overwrite%20centuries%20of%20Islamic%20influence%20on%20Indian%20culture%2C%20names%2C%20and%20places.%20The%20ideal%20of%20inter-faith%20co-existence%20in%20harmony%20has%20been%20jettisoned%3B%20the%20marginalisation%20of%20Muslims%20from%20the%20national%20narrative%20marches%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20Just%20An%20Indian%20Problem%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20historical%20revisionism%20is%20not%20uniquely%20Indian.%20From%20the%20United%20States%2C%20where%20radical%20leftist%20movements%20sought%20to%20dismantle%20statues%20and%20monuments%20deemed%20symbols%20of%20white%20supremacy%2C%20to%20European%20debates%20over%20colonial-era%20relics%2C%20and%20black%20and%20brown%20Britons%20toppling%20statues%20of%20colonial%20oppressors%2C%20the%20impulse%20to%20wield%20history%20as%20a%20weapon%20in%20contemporary%20politics%20is%20universal.%20Still%2C%20there%20is%20surely%20a%20case%20for%20India%20reconciling%20with%20the%20past%20rather%20than%20seeking%20endlessly%20to%20undo%20it%20-%20for%20moderation%20over%20hysteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20lies%20in%20the%20unrelenting%20politicisation%20of%20history.%20If%20one%20faction%20tears%20down%20Aurangzeb's%20legacy%2C%20another%20rises%20to%20defend%20it.%20If%20one%20renames%20a%20city%20to%20honour%20a%20Hindu%20king%20(Chhatrapati%20Sambhajinagar)%20or%20a%20Hindu%20civilisational%20tradition%20(Prayagraj)%2C%20another%20questions%20the%20relevance%20of%20doing%20so%2C%20asking%20whether%20there%20is%20no%20comfort%20to%20be%20had%20in%20the%20familiarity%20of%20place%20names%20established%20on%20our%20coil%20over%20centuries.%20The%20pendulum%20swings%20incessantly%2C%20with%20no%20resolution%20in%20sight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20path%20forward%20must%20embody%20a%20mature%20relationship%20with%20its%20past%20-%20one%20that%20neither%20erases%20nor%20glorifies%2C%20but%20contextualises.%20This%20journey%20requires%20empathy%2C%20introspection%2C%20and%20a%20willingness%20to%20transcend%20ideological%20boundaries.%20History%2C%20after%20all%2C%20should%20enlighten%2C%20not%20enchain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20alternative%20is%20a%20nightmare.%20One%20day%2C%20the%20Muslims%20of%20India%20will%20resist.%20Once%20again%2C%20the%20violence%20will%20resume%2C%20spawning%20new%20hostages%20to%20history%2C%20ensuring%20that%20future%20generations%20would%20be%20taught%20new%20wrongs%20to%20set%20right.%20The%20fanatics%20and%20extremists%20are%20happy%20to%20use%20history%20as%20cannon%20fodder%3B%20but%20in%20their%20obsession%20with%20undoing%20the%20past%2C%20it%20is%20our%20future%20they%20are%20placing%20in%20peril.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(%3Cem%3EShashi%20Tharoor%20has%20been%20a%20Member%20of%20Parliament%20from%20Thiruvananthapuram%2C%20Kerala%2C%20since%202009.%20He%20is%20a%20published%20author%20and%20a%20former%20diplomat.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743833940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F2rb3e83c_aurangzeb_625x300_05_April_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Faurangzeb-the-ghosts-of-history-and-the-politics-of-remembrance-8091909%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ideological%20battle%20unfolding%20today%2C%20whether%20over%20Aurangzeb%20or%20the%20broader%20legacy%20of%20Islamic%20rule%2C%20reflects%20the%20interplay%20between%20history%20and%20nationalism.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Faurangzeb-the-ghosts-of-history-and-the-politics-of-remembrance-8091909%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tata%20Capital%20files%20for%20confidential%20IPO%20with%20Sebi%2C%20eyes%20%E2%82%B915%2C000%20cr%20listing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743833916000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fipo%2Ftata-capital-files-confidential-ipo-with-sebi-15000-crore-listing-125040500265_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tata%20Capital's%20board%20approved%20the%20IPO%2C%20comprising%20a%20fresh%20issue%20of%20up%20to%20230%20million%20shares%20along%20with%20an%20offer%20for%20sale%20by%20existing%20shareholders%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'There%E2%80%99s%20a%20permanent%20government'%3A%20Eric%20Adams%20believes%20in%20the%20'deep%20state'%20theory%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743833446000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-120004571%2Cimg